<div class="generic seventsixty">
   <h1>Watercoolr</h1>
  <strong class="tagline">pubsub via webhooks, or "twitter" for your applications</strong>

	<p>This is a public server, feel free to use it to power your own HTTP pubsub services!</p>
<br/>
<br/>
<div class="example">
<h4>Example:</h4>
<strong>Create a channel:</strong>
<pre>
&rarr; POST /channels
&larr; { 'id':'2d0128d' }
</pre>
<br/>
<strong>Add subscribers:</strong>
<pre>
&rarr; POST /subscribers data={ 'channel':'2d0128d', 'url':'http://api.otherservice.com/your-message-handler' }
&larr; { 'status': 'OK' }
</pre>
<br/>
<strong>Post messages:</strong>
<pre>
you &rarr; POST /messages data={ 'channel':'2d0128d', 'message':'hey guys!' }
   us &rarr; POST http://api.otherservice.com/your-message-handler data='hey guys!'
   ...for every subscriber...
&larr; { 'status': 'OK' }
</pre>
<br/>
<h4>This server is powered by <a href="http://github.com/igrigorik/watercoolr">modified GAE version</a> of <a href="http://www.github.com/jcapote/watercoolr">watercoolr service</a>.</h4>
</div>
</div>
</div>

